      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here are three quick archetypal profiles to help ground your gritty series:\n\n1.  **The Ironclad Crew**: A tight-knit Latino street gang based in Houston, Texas, led by a stoic, immigrant-born vice kingpin with a deep-seated code of honor that clashes with their violent methods. They thrive in low-income, inner-city neighborhoods where trust is scarce, yet their loyalty binds them tighter than any criminal contract.\n\n2.  **The Velvet Cage**: A homogeneous group of white, power-hungry CEOs operating a shadow fund from a penthouse office overlooking downtown Chicago. These cold, calculated execs wear tailored suits and speak in cryptic financial jargon, masking their drug trafficking syndicate behind a facade of charity and skyscraper architecture.\n\n3.  **The Suburban Saviors**: A disillusioned white family living on the edge of the unspoiled Pacific Northwest suburbs, where they hide their involvement in a real estate murder-for-hire racket between husband and son. They possess a quiet, performative gentility, but their love for their neglected daughters is the only thing that grounds them against the creeping corruption of their affluent neighborhood.",
